
9:33 AM
Hostname: pln-ipamaster.ipa.calix.local

Describe the impact to you or the business:

Critical production risk. We are migrating our sole IPA CA master from RHEL 8 (cpeg-ipareplica.ipa.calix.local, IPA 4.9.13) to RHEL 9 (pln-ipamaster.ipa.calix.local, IPA 4.12.2) ahead of a mandatory datacenter shutdown on March 28, 2026. The source server cpeg will be powered off at that time. If the migration is not complete before then, we will experience a complete authentication outage across thousands of IPA-joined systems — SSH logins, sudo, LDAP, and certificate services will all stop working.

The ipa-replica-install command completed all CA steps successfully but failed at the final step with: wait_for_entry timeout on ldap://cpeg-ipareplica.ipa.calix.local:389 for cn=KDC,cn=pln-ipamaster.ipa.calix.local,cn=masters,cn=ipa,cn=etc,dc=ipa,dc=calix,dc=local

All services on pln (DS, pki-tomcatd, krb5kdc, httpd) are running. sysrestore.state shows complete=False. We cannot uninstall and retry as the CA database replication takes 5+ hours. We need to complete this installation without a full reinstall.

In what environment:

Production. Single IPA realm IPA.CALIX.LOCAL. Source: cpeg-ipareplica.ipa.calix.local RHEL 8.x IPA 4.9.13, sole CA master and CRL generator. Target: pln-ipamaster.ipa.calix.local RHEL 9.3 IPA 4.12.2. Pre-existing CSN purge issues on the changelog. Replication from pln to cpeg shows Error 18 transient warning — incremental update backing off. Replication from cpeg to pln works fine.

How frequently:

Occurs every install attempt. We have attempted the replica install multiple times over several days. The failure point is always the same — the cn=KDC entry written to pln's LDAP does not replicate to cpeg within the timeout window due to the Error 18 replication issue on the pln to cpeg agreement.

Summary: ipa-replica-install fails with wait_for_entry timeout on cn=KDC — cannot complete RHEL 8 to RHEL 9 IPA migration before critical deadline
Environment:

Source: cpeg-ipareplica.ipa.calix.local — RHEL 8, IPA 4.9.13, sole CA master
Target: pln-ipamaster.ipa.calix.local — RHEL 9.3, IPA 4.12.2
Hard deadline: March 28 Petaluma DC shutdown — cpeg goes offline

What happened:

ipa-replica-install --setup-ca got through all CA steps successfully (steps 1-33 complete including CA startup)
Failed at final step: wait_for_entry timeout on ldap://cpeg-ipareplica.ipa.calix.local:389 for cn=KDC,cn=pln-ipamaster.ipa.calix.local,cn=masters,cn=ipa,cn=etc,dc=ipa,dc=calix,dc=local
The cn=KDC entry exists on pln but never replicates to cpeg
Root cause: pln → cpeg replication agreement shows Error (18) Can't acquire replica (Incremental update) due to pre-existing CSN purge issue on the changelog
cpeg → pln replication works fine (Error 0)

Current state:

pln has DS, CA (pki-tomcatd), KDC, httpd all running
sysrestore.state shows complete = False
Cannot uninstall pln — CA database took 5+ hours to replicate
Cannot re-initialize cpeg from pln — cpeg is the only working IPA master

What we need:

How to manually complete the replica install or mark it complete after manually injecting the missing cn=masters entries into cpeg
Or how to fix the Error (18) incremental replication from pln to cpeg so the KDC entry pushes over

Severity: Urgent — production IPA outage if not resolved before March 28




# Full replication status
ldapsearch -Y EXTERNAL -H ldapi://%2Frun%2Fslapd-IPA-CALIX-LOCAL.socket \
  -b "cn=meTocpeg-ipareplica.ipa.calix.local,cn=replica,cn=dc\3Dipa\2Cdc\3Dcalix\2Cdc\3Dlocal,cn=mapping tree,cn=config" \
  -s base "(objectclass=*)" 2>/dev/null > /tmp/pln-repl-agreement.txt

# Last 500 lines of install log
tail -500 /var/log/ipareplica-install.log > /tmp/pln-install-log.txt

# DS errors log
tail -1000 /var/log/dirsrv/slapd-IPA-CALIX-LOCAL/errors > /tmp/pln-ds-errors.txt

# sysrestore state
cp /var/lib/ipa/sysrestore/sysrestore.state /tmp/pln-sysrestore.txt

# IPA version
ipa --version > /tmp/pln-ipa-version.txt


# Full replication agreements
ldapsearch -Y EXTERNAL -H ldapi://%2Frun%2Fslapd-IPA-CALIX-LOCAL.socket \
  -b "cn=config" "(objectclass=nsds5replicationagreement)" 2>/dev/null > /tmp/cpeg-repl-agreements.txt

# DS errors log
tail -1000 /var/log/dirsrv/slapd-IPA-CALIX-LOCAL/errors > /tmp/cpeg-ds-errors.txt

# IPA version
ipa --version > /tmp/cpeg-ipa-version.txt
